Exchanges that used to be self-policing institutions dedicated to clean and transparent markets are now public. They make their money on the volume generated by high-frequency and quant strategies and products, selling special data feeds to the perpetrators of this mess.

It is imperative that the SEC evaluate the harmful impact of non levered and leveraged ETFs and quant strategies and products for the purpose of creating needed regulations before our markets are further undermined.
